Sec. 146.024. ABANDONED ANIMALS. (a) In order to satisfy
unpaid fees and debts to the state and private suppliers, the
department may sell at public auction an animal that the owner leaves
in the processing facilities for more than 30 days.
(b) The proceeds of a sale under this section shall be used
first to satisfy the fees owed to the department and then to satisfy
the fees and debts owed to private suppliers. Any balance of the
proceeds shall be paid to the owner of the animal, as determined by
the manifest or shipping order accompanying the animal.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1368, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

